---
import BaseLayout from '@layouts/BaseLayout.astro';

// CONFIGURE ME: set to your Cal.com slug once the account is set up.
// e.g. 'ishmukit/intro-call'
const CAL_COM_LINK = 'ishmukit/intro-call';
---
<BaseLayout
  title="C8 — Finance that thinks forward. For SMEs that have outgrown their accountant."
  description="Senior finance expertise for UK SMEs. Fractional finance director services from an ex-VW, Mercedes and VW Financial Services finance leader. Forecasts, models, management reporting — layered above your existing accountant."
  pageType="home"
>

<!-- HERO -->
<section class="hero">
  <div class="container">
    <h1 class="reveal" style="margin-top:8px">Finance that <span class="accent">thinks forward</span>. For SMEs that have outgrown their accountant.</h1>
    <p class="sub reveal">I'm the senior finance partner for UK SMEs that need more than a bookkeeper — but aren't ready for a £130k in-house finance director. Think of me as the strategic finance person inside the business. Not filing the past. Planning the future.</p>

    <div class="hero-outcomes reveal">
      <span class="tag">Know if you can afford to hire</span>
      <span class="tag">Spot cash problems before they hit</span>
      <span class="tag">Walk into investor meetings with numbers that hold up</span>
      <span class="tag">See which customers actually make you money</span>
      <span class="tag">Price with confidence, not guesswork</span>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-ctas reveal">
      <a href="#contact" class="btn btn-primary">Book a 20-min intro <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      <a href="#magnet" class="btn btn-secondary">Free cash-flow template</a>
    </div>

    <div class="hero-metrics reveal">
      <div class="m"><div class="num" data-count="2.25" data-decimals="2" data-prefix="£">£0<span class="unit">m+</span></div><div class="lbl">Raised for C8 clients through investor-ready models</div></div>
      <div class="m"><div class="num" data-count="34">0<span class="unit">%</span></div><div class="lbl">Gross profit lift after one pricing restructure</div></div>
      <div class="m"><div class="num" data-count="20">0<span class="unit">%</span></div><div class="lbl">Cost base cut in three months, no layoffs</div></div>
      <div class="m"><div class="num" data-count="13">0<span class="unit">+ yrs</span></div><div class="lbl">Senior finance across FTSE-listed and high-growth businesses</div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CREDIBILITY -->
<section class="creds" aria-label="Past employers">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="lbl">A decade running budgets, forecasts and business cases inside</div>
    <div class="creds-row">
      <div class="co">Volkswagen</div>
      <div class="co">Mercedes-Benz</div>
      <div class="co">VW Financial Services</div>
      <div class="co">Virgin Active</div>
      <div class="co">Avon</div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PROBLEM -->
<section class="problem">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">If any of this sounds familiar</span>
      <h2>The questions most SME owners can't answer with <span>confidence</span>.</h2>
      <p>Every one of these is a sign your finance setup has run out of road. Not a crisis — just the point where an accountant alone isn't enough anymore.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="problems">
      <div class="p-card reveal"><div class="num">01</div><div class="body"><h3>"How long do I actually have before I run out of cash?"</h3><p class="ask">Your bookkeeper can tell you what's in the bank today. Not what it looks like in six months under a bad quarter.</p><div class="fix">I build a live 13-week cash forecast so you see the cliff before you fall off it.</div></div></div>
      <div class="p-card reveal"><div class="num">02</div><div class="body"><h3>"Can I afford to hire this person?"</h3><p class="ask">A salary isn't a salary — it's national insurance, pension, equipment, ramp-up time. Without a model, you're guessing with other people's wages.</p><div class="fix">I model the true cost of the hire and tell you exactly what it does to your runway.</div></div></div>
      <div class="p-card reveal"><div class="num">03</div><div class="body"><h3>"Which customers or products are actually making me money?"</h3><p class="ask">Your accounts show one gross margin. Real life has five. Most SMEs discover their biggest customer is their worst margin once someone actually looks.</p><div class="fix">I break the business down by product, customer and channel so you see where the profit actually lives.</div></div></div>
      <div class="p-card reveal"><div class="num">04</div><div class="body"><h3>"Will a bank or investor take my numbers seriously?"</h3><p class="ask">Investors and lenders can tell in 30 seconds whether your model was built by a founder or a finance pro. They act accordingly.</p><div class="fix">I build the model and the narrative the way I built them for boards at VW and Mercedes — so when it's in front of someone sceptical, it holds up.</div></div></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SOLUTIONS -->
<section class="solutions">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">How I help</span>
      <h2>Three ways C8 works <span>inside your business</span>.</h2>
      <p>Layer any one on top of your existing accountant, or combine all three. What you get is the strategic finance brain a full-time FD would bring — sized for where you are now.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="sol-grid">
      <div class="sol reveal"><div class="sol-num">01</div><h3>Like a senior finance lead, on tap.</h3><p>The person inside the business thinking about the money — not just filing it. Monthly reviews where we step back from the day-to-day and look at where you're going. Someone to call before you make a big decision.</p><ul class="sol-list"><li>Monthly strategic review meetings</li><li>Ad-hoc support on big decisions</li><li>Translating the numbers into the next move</li></ul><a href="#contact" class="sol-link">Start here <span class="arrow">→</span></a></div>
      <div class="sol reveal featured"><div class="sol-num">02</div><h3>Numbers you can actually trust.</h3><p>Real forecasts and management accounts that tell you what's coming — not just what happened. Built around how YOUR business works, not a generic template. Updated monthly so you're never making decisions on last year's information.</p><ul class="sol-list"><li>Rolling 12-month forecast with scenarios</li><li>Monthly management accounts and variance analysis</li><li>KPI dashboard — one screen, the whole business</li></ul><a href="#contact" class="sol-link">Explore <span class="arrow">→</span></a></div>
      <div class="sol reveal"><div class="sol-num">03</div><h3>Ready when growth calls.</h3><p>When a bank, investor, or board starts asking questions, your numbers need to survive real scrutiny. I build models the way I built them at VW and Mercedes — so when someone pokes, they hold up.</p><ul class="sol-list"><li>Investor-grade pitch models and narrative</li><li>Bank-loan applications with proper forecasts</li><li>Due diligence support and board-ready reporting</li></ul><a href="#contact" class="sol-link">Explore <span class="arrow">→</span></a></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- SERVICES / TIERS -->
<section class="services" id="services">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">Three stages of growing up financially</span>
      <h2>Pick the tier that <span>fits where you are</span>.</h2>
      <p>Each tier is built around the outcomes you need at that stage — not a shopping list of deliverables. Move up as the business grows.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="tiers">
      <div class="tier reveal">
        <div class="tname">Clarity</div>
        <div class="fit">// For SMEs that want to stop flying blind</div>
        <p class="lead">You've got a bookkeeper. The accounts get filed. But you can't confidently answer "am I making money this month?" or "will I have enough cash in Q4?" — and that's costing you sleep.</p>
        <ul class="t-list">
          <li>Know where the money's going every month</li>
          <li>Spot cash-flow trouble months before it hits</li>
          <li>See if the hiring/spending plan actually works</li>
          <li>One simple dashboard that tells you if the business is healthy</li>
          <li>A monthly hour to talk through what the numbers mean</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn">Explore Clarity <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
      <div class="tier featured reveal">
        <div class="badge">Most chosen</div>
        <div class="tname">Momentum</div>
        <div class="fit">// For SMEs raising, borrowing or scaling deliberately</div>
        <p class="lead">You've got traction. Now you want to raise, borrow, or put the foot down — and you need the numbers to survive scrutiny from someone who'll test them.</p>
        <ul class="t-list">
          <li>Walk into investor or bank meetings knowing your model holds up</li>
          <li>See which products, customers and channels actually make money</li>
          <li>Test pricing and scenarios before committing to them</li>
          <li>Board-ready monthly reporting — not spreadsheets you're embarrassed to send</li>
          <li>Quarterly strategy workshop to plan ahead, not react</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn">Explore Momentum <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
      <div class="tier reveal">
        <div class="tname">Infrastructure</div>
        <div class="fit">// For established SMEs ready for a proper finance function</div>
        <p class="lead">You've been running a while. You're doing well. Finance is now a real bottleneck — you need something closer to an in-house finance team, without the £130k hire.</p>
        <ul class="t-list">
          <li>Build the finance setup you'd have at 3x your current size</li>
          <li>Board-grade reporting your leadership team can act on</li>
          <li>Know exactly where to invest next based on data, not gut</li>
          <li>Plan and advise on hiring your first in-house finance staff</li>
          <li>Monthly exec-level review with ad-hoc strategic support</li>
        </ul>
        <a href="#contact" class="btn">Explore Infrastructure <span class="arrow">→</span></a>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- ABOUT -->
<section class="about" id="about">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="about-grid">
      <div class="reveal">
        <span class="eyebrow">Why me</span>
        <h2>I learned finance where the <em>numbers matter</em>.</h2>
        <div class="story">
          <p>I'm Ish. I'm an ACCA-qualified finance leader with 13+ years inside FTSE-listed and high-growth businesses. I spent six years inside Volkswagen Financial Services running £600m of annual budgets and 5-year forecasts — cutting £14m of costs, halving our forecasting cycle, and writing a £60m business case that got adopted across European markets.</p>
          <p>Before that, I ran financial planning for IT and HR at Mercedes-Benz Financial Services — owning the variance analysis on a £120m budget.</p>
          <p>I started C8 because SME owners kept asking me the same finance questions their accountants couldn't answer. Now I do for UK SMEs what I used to do for blue-chips — just on a budget that makes sense for a growing business.</p>
        </div>
        <div class="signature">Ish Mukit — ACCA<small>Founder, C8</small></div>
      </div>
      <div class="about-stats reveal">
        <div class="s"><div class="big"><span class="accent">£600</span>m</div><div class="txt">Annual budgets directed at Volkswagen Financial Services</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="big"><span class="accent">£60</span>m</div><div class="txt">Business case I led to German HQ — adopted Europe-wide</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="big"><span class="accent">£14</span>m</div><div class="txt">Cost savings delivered at VWFS through cost analysis</div></div>
        <div class="s"><div class="big"><span class="accent">13</span>+ yrs</div><div class="txt">Senior finance across blue-chips and high-growth businesses</div></div>
      </div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- CASE STUDIES -->
<section class="cases" id="cases">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">What clients have seen</span>
      <h2>Real outcomes. <span style="color:var(--lime)">Real businesses</span>.</h2>
      <p>Names anonymised where the client prefers it. The point isn't the logo — it's what changed after I got hold of the numbers.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="case-grid">
      <article class="case reveal">
        <div class="sector">Consulting firm</div>
        <div class="big"><em>+34%</em></div>
        <h3>Gross profit in three months</h3>
        <p>One underperforming product line. Pulled the numbers apart, restructured the pricing model based on actual margin data, relaunched — 34% more gross profit within a quarter.</p>
      </article>
      <article class="case reveal">
        <div class="sector">High-growth startup</div>
        <div class="big">£750k<em> raised</em></div>
        <h3>Seed round, closed with confidence</h3>
        <p>Built the driver-based model, wrote the pitch narrative, and led investor calls alongside the founders. Every question got a real answer — not "let me come back to you on that".</p>
      </article>
      <article class="case reveal">
        <div class="sector">Growing consultancy</div>
        <div class="big"><em>-20%</em></div>
        <h3>Cost base, three months in</h3>
        <p>No layoffs, no cuts to anything customer-facing. Just three months of "where does this £ actually go" and a few structural changes. Costs down 20%, profit up, same team.</p>
      </article>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- PROCESS -->
<section class="process">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="section-head reveal">
      <span class="eyebrow">How we'd work together</span>
      <h2>Four stages. <span>No surprises</span>.</h2>
      <p>From first call to working with me as your embedded finance lead — here's what it actually looks like.</p>
    </div>
    <div class="steps">
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="dot">01</div><h3>Intro call</h3><p>20 minutes. You explain where you're at. I tell you honestly if I can help — and if I can't, I'll point you at someone who can.</p></div>
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="dot">02</div><h3>Scope &amp; fit</h3><p>I write a short scope and a fixed monthly fee. You know exactly what you're getting and what you're paying before we start.</p></div>
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="dot">03</div><h3>Setup sprint</h3><p>First two to four weeks. I build your forecast, reporting and model from scratch — shaped around your business, not a template.</p></div>
      <div class="step reveal"><div class="dot">04</div><h3>Monthly rhythm</h3><p>Monthly review meeting, live model updates, email and Slack access between times. You focus on the business. I focus on the numbers.</p></div>
    </div>
  </div>
</section>

<!-- LEAD MAGNET -->
<section class="magnet" id="magnet">
  <div class="container">
    <div class="wrap reveal">
      <div>
        <span class="eyebrow" style="color:var(--lime)">Free resource</span>
        <h2>The cash-flow model I actually <em>use</em> with clients.</h2>
        <p>A 13-week rolling cash-flow template in Excel. Same structure I set up for a new client in week one. Scenarios, sensitivities, visual warnings when you're heading for trouble. Yours free.</p>
        <form name="lead-magnet" method="POST" data-netlify="true" netlify-honeypot="bot-field" action="/thanks">
          <input type="hidden" name="form-name" value="lead-magnet" />
          <input type="text" name="bot-field" style="display:none" />
          <input type="email" name="email" placeholder="your@email.com" required aria-label="Email address" />
          <button type="submit" class="btn">Send me the template</button>
        </form>
        <p style="margin-top:16px;font-size:13px;opacity:0.5">No spam. One-click unsubscribe. Occasional short emails on SME finance that you'll actually want to read.</p>
      </div>
